'''Ross’ syndrome''' consists of [[Adie's syndrome]] (myotonic [[pupil]]s and absent deep [[tendon]] reflexes) plus segmental [[anhidrosis]] (typically associated with compensatory [[hyperhidrosis]]).<ref name="Bolognia">{{cite book |author=Rapini, Ronald P.; Bolognia, Jean L.; Jorizzo, Joseph L. |title=Dermatology: 2-Volume Set |publisher=Mosby |location=St. Louis |year=2007 |pages=539 |isbn=1-4160-2999-0 |oclc= |doi= |accessdate=}}</ref>

It was characterized in 1958<ref name="Braun-Falco2000">{{cite book|author=Otto Braun-Falco|title=Dermatology|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=HkOty7O_KlkC&pg=PA1093|accessdate=20 November 2010|year=2000|publisher=Springer|isbn=978-3-540-59452-9|pages=1093–}}</ref><ref name="pmid20408939">{{cite journal |author=Yaşar S, Aslan C, Serdar ZA, Demirci GT, Tutkavul K, Babalik D |title=Ross syndrome: Unilateral hyperhidrosis, Adie's tonic pupils and diffuse areflexia |journal=J Dtsch Dermatol Ges |volume= 8|issue= 12|pages= 1004–1006|year=2010 |month=April |pmid=20408939 |doi=10.1111/j.1610-0387.2010.07400.x }}</ref> by A.T. Ross.<ref name="pmid13590391">{{cite journal |author=Ross AT |title=Progressive selective sudomotor denervation; a case with coexisting Adie's syndrome |journal=Neurology |volume=8 |issue=11 |pages=809–17 |year=1958 |month=November |pmid=13590391 |doi= |url=}}</ref>

As of 1992, 18 cases had been documented.<ref name="pmid1597691">{{cite journal |author=Weller M, Wilhelm H, Sommer N, Dichgans J, Wiethölter H |title=Tonic pupil, areflexia, and segmental anhidrosis: two additional cases of Ross syndrome and review of the literature |journal=J. Neurol. |volume=239 |issue=4 |pages=231–4 |year=1992 |month=April |pmid=1597691 |doi= 10.1007/BF00839146|url=}}</ref>

